description: Number of partitions of n into parts 6k+3 or 6k+5.
formula: a(n) ~ exp(Pi*sqrt(2*n)/3) * Gamma(5/6) / (4 * 2^(1/12) * sqrt(3) * Pi^(1/6) * n^(11/12)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 27 2015
mathematica: nmax = 100; Rest[CoefficientList[Series[Product[1/((1 - x^(6k+3))*(1 - x^(6k+5))), {k, 0, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x]] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 27 2015 *)
